= Logarithmen

$a^(log_a (x)) = x$ \
$log_a (1) = 0$ weil a hoch was ist 1 \
$log_a (a) = 1$ \
$log_a (x/y) = log_a (x) - log_a (y)$ \
$log_a (x*y) = log_a (x) + log_a (y)$ \
$log_a (x^p) = log_a (|x|) * p, p % 2 = 0$ \
$log_a (root(n,x)) = log_a (x^(1/n)) = 1/n log_a (x) $ \
$(log_a (b^y))/(log_a (b)) = (y log_a (b))/(log_a (b))$ \
$log_a(x) = -2 <=> a^(-2) = x$

